rComments: He is a joke.  All bluster.  Fools a few people, but his is all about self-promotion.
knows a ton and is really helpful if you really want to talk about art history!

He has got to be the worst teacher I have ever had.  I love art history with a passion, I got a degree in it, but I fell asleep whenever he started talking.  He is everything that is wrong with the art world today, it's a farce.

He was never there for help because he was out promoting his book. His TA's have to be some of the worst and all of them think highly of themselves and look down to everybody else. Very unclear class. It made me hate Art History and cause me never to take an Art History Class at the U of I!

Professor Fineburg's Class was a nightmare, I have never taken art history before, so the amount of material we had to know for exams was rediculous. An endless amt of notecards did not help. Plus his TA's were not forgiving at all....in other words ANAL

This was my first ever art history (and art anything, for that matter) course, and it's been an awesome learning experience.  Fineburg seems like some sort of all-knowing art god.  This course is DEFinitely worth it if you're willing to put your time into it.
awsome professor and great guy! highly recommend getting to know him or taking a class of his!!!
